-- Pimco Total Return Fund had net outflows of $3.9 bln in August - Morningstar
-- 
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 10:42AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Sept 3 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund run by Bill Gross, had net outflows of $3.9 billion in August, marking the 16th straight month of outflows, according to Morningstar on Wednesday.

The Pimco Total Return Fund had $221.6 billion in assets under management at the end of August, Morningstar added.